Sternum without posterior tubercle. Abdomen higher than long, forming a large dorsal hump (
Figure 176
). Carapace dark brown, central area slightly lighter with diffuse radial stripes. Chelicerae and gnathocoxae light brown. Sternum light brown with thin dark margins and small dark spots. Legs and pedipalps light yellow with dark patches and annulations. Abdomen whitish to greyish brown, with white guanin areas; on dorsum a pair of distinct white stripes outline an irregular, broad band, branching laterally and ending before tip of abdomen; area behind these stripes lighter than anterior area. From apex a clear white median stripe leads straight to spinnerets. Aboral area of abdomen whitish with two transverse, strongly upwardly bent dark stripes. Venter dark and white speckled. Spinnerets light brown.

Known only from an import from tropical Africa (
Democratic Republic of Congo
) without exact locality (
Schmidt 1957
).
